			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				As others have mentioned, crusaders can spawn in many places in CT.  Most of the ones I have seen have been in the temple floor or &quot;4 corners&quot;.  There is usually a &quot;roamer&quot; in addition to the static spawns in each corner.  Occasionally this roamer is a crusader.  3 of the 4 crusaders i have seen/killed were these roamers. <BR>
<BR>
Also, don't worry so much about the HT.  If you are an SK and are a high enough level to be hunting crusaders you can take the HT.  My first crusader kill was at level 27 and he harm touched me for about 2 bubbles of HP (total HP about 850).  This is with a moderate magic resist of 60.  If this makes you nervous, you should probably wait a few levels or buy your dark forge.
				</font>
