			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I did not hunt here until thirtieth lvl. If you're an sk and want to kill crusaders, it is difficult<BR>
without gather shadows. At 30 lvl you easily get exp from the gators. But, the gators have <BR>
no loot, except for the mage quest items, and, chunks o' meat(free food). At 34 lvl, killed a <BR>
crusader near the top of the archon pyramid, or, rather my group did. We were full group <BR>
of low 30's. But, a ninja looting necro in the group got the decayed stuff, for his sk &quot;twink&quot;. <BR>
Killed another crusader in the sewers. I got 1 decayed gauntlet and 1 decayed legplate. <BR>
You must have invis to pass all the greenies to get where the crusaders spawn, or, if you <BR>
have a powerful group, just kill them all. My pet accidentally aggroed some greenies and <BR>
we killed everything in the maze, which is pretty much half the zone. Swimming ability a <BR>
plus here. If you don't have high swimming ability when you get to Cazic, you soon will.<BR>
Especially if you're a tank, and a puller. One more thing, stun and bash save your butt <BR>
here. If noone in your group can bash or stun you will be running to zone from all the <BR>
lizardman healers. Actually, you need 2 people in group to bash and stun. The named <BR>
lizardmen in the throneroom are enchanters and they will charm, it always seems to be<BR>
a tank that they charm. Someone trained the tae ew diviner to the zone, where I<BR>
happened to be. I killed several ppl in their 20's before I came out of it. Boy, were they <BR>
peeooo'ed.<BR>
<BR>
Thanatolian Phatrat<BR>
35 sk<BR>
&lt;The Embraced&gt;<BR>
