	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Greetings and Well Met all, especially to those who know the true glories and creative powers of Hatred, Chaos, Fear, and Blight.<BR>
<BR>
My name, or rather I am called, Vandyyr Shayol.  I am a servant of Innoruuk and none other (on the Rathe), and a mighty Dark Knight.<BR>
<BR>
However, due to the tests of Innoruuk, I have been forced to complete my Darkforge twice, and may have to complete it again - he has a tendancy to summon me to Hate, give me instructions, and tells me to carry them out without the equipment I had gathered to that point (that's basically my roleplaying for EQ bugs took my equipment twice and I've had to get it all back cuz the GMs won't do anything).<BR>
<BR>
The first time I completed my suit of Darkforge Armor I was only in my 24th season, and it was a new creation borne of my Lord's Hatred.  I was told to enter Cazic Thule and slay those shadowknights who followed that god and take their spoils to Mistmoore and Najena.  To my surprise, the gorillas at the time were dropping the decaying armor (apparently finding some of the crusaders looking like bananas), and I was able to complete my set of decayed there, and through the aide of some of my companions, the other pieces to the armor that I would require.  (This was due to an early bug that allowed the gorillas in TR1 to drop the decaying, but the Crusaders were not, made for much easier completion times, but unfortuneately this bug has been corrected.).<BR>
<BR>
But alas, all was lost after my First Calling.  And I was bade to return to Cazic Thule in my 30th season to reclaim my suit, which took me many days and nights with several companions near the Temple of the Archon.  I never fully completed the second set, falling short by a pair of bracers, but that problem was remedied later - something for another tale I suppose.<BR>
<BR>
I can tell you that the Crusaders are one of the hardest parts of the Darkforge Armor quest.  Their God has imbued them with great abilities, such that they do indeed become a dangerous foe.  However, the problem of their harm touch can be easily remedied with a good cleric or necromancer - either of which can use their limited invulnerability spells to absorb the hit - or by sending your worthless pet into the fray first.  True, good ol' Kabober will not be able to aid you much after he takes that damage, but then your hide is not blistering by the effects of the magick now either is it?  If you have a good group and can control the temple grounds, you will find that the Archon and the lizzies will send several of their dark warriors to cleanse their temples, and you can regain their armor.  But remember my brethren, that is only the beginning - or the end, depending - of the quest you have started.  The guards of the human realms are very formidable foes, and you must kill at least three of them!  Not to mention that you must venture forth into the lands of our lighter cousins - or &quot;da elfsies&quot; to the trolls and ogres out there - to recover some items from those fabled lands!  Beware my brethren, the path you take here is frought with danger, but behold the fruits of your labors should you succeed, they will allow you to spread Innoruuk's Hatred most effectively!<BR>
<BR>
Vandyyr Shayol<BR>
Dark Knight of Innoruuk
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
